Description: Fragment of shallow pottery bowl, with ledge rim. Fine light tan clay with some large white inclusions. Wheel-incised grooves on outer wall. Two post-firing suspension holes. Incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 458)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.723)
